S018.question: Equilibrated weight-1000
S018.question_instruction: Equilibrated weight-1000. Numeric variable [makes the sample size of all countries equal to the same amount of N=1000]. Equilibrated weights have been calculated using the formula: 1.000/sample size. Equilibrated weight can be used when all countries and territories involved in the analysis are required to be treated as equal units, regardless of their population or sample size.
